By Ahmed AbbaDamaturu. -. The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) Yobe, is fully ready for the Governorship and State House of Assembly elections scheduled to hold nationwide on March 9, 2019. The State Commandant, Mr Ayinla Olowo, made this known in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Damaturu on Thursday. “We are fully ready and properly mobilised for the Governorship and State House of Assembly elections. “The testimony of this command’s effort by members of the public remains one of the strong motivation factors for the command to perform and discharge its duties diligently and more professionally, ‘’ Olowo said. He commended the people of the state for conducting themselves well in the previous elections and enjoined them to maintain same in the next elections. Olowo also urged the electorate to go out freely and vote for candidates of their choice, saying the command in collaboration with other sister agencies were ready to protect their lives and property.  (